import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='price', by='symbol', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of stock prices across all companies?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Company')
    ax.set_ylabel('Stock Price')
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.legend(title='Companies', loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    for company in data['symbol'].unique():
        company_data = data[data['symbol'] == company]
        ax.plot(company_data['date'], company_data['price'], label=company)
    
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of stock prices for each company over time?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Stock Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    avg_prices = data.groupby('symbol')['price'].mean()
    ax = avg_prices.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'orange', 'green', 'red', 'purple'])
    
    plt.title('What is the average stock price for each company?')
    plt.xlabel('Company')
    plt.ylabel('Average Stock Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(avg_prices.index, title='Companies')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    companies = data['symbol'].unique()
    colors = ['blue', 'green', 'red', 'orange', 'purple']
    
    for i, company in enumerate(companies):
        company_data = data[data['symbol'] == company]
        plt.scatter(company_data['date'], company_data['price'], color=colors[i], label=company)
    
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Stock Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Company')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between stock prices of different companies?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='price', hue='symbol', kde=True, bins=30)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of stock prices for each company?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Stock Price')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(title='Company', loc='upper right')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
